<h2>Welcome to the latex2edx demo course</h2>

<p>This is a sample course generated from a latex source file,
  compiled into <a href="http://data.edx.org">edX XML</a>
  using <a href="https://github.com/mitocw/latex2edx">latex2edx</a>. Content
  includes examples of basic problems, text, and video modules, as
  well as advanced problems using custom graders written in python,
  and graphical input via javascript.</p>

<p>Examples:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Numerical_response_with_inline_labels">Numerical
	    response with inline labels</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Custom_response">Custom response problem with two
    inputs</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Formula_response">Formula response problem checking
    mathematical equations</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Matrix_expression_equality">Matrix expression equality
    testing</a> (for math expressions with nonabelian operators)</li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Quantum_mechanics_ket_input">Quantum mechanics ket input</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Adaptive_hints">Adaptive hints</a> using "hint_fn"
  scripts</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Drag_and_drop_problem_created_via_latex2dnd">Drag and drop problem created via latex2dnd</a></li>
<li><a href="/course/jump_to_id/Graphical_input_via_jsxgraph">Graphical input via jsxgraph</a> (using the
	     jsinput framework and customresponse)</li>
</ul>

<p>See the <a href="https://github.com/mitocw/latex2edx">latex2edx distribution</a> 
and the <a href="https://github.com/mitocw/latex2dnd">latex2dnd package</a> 
for more information.</p>

<p>The source code for this course is here: <a href="https://github.com/mitocw/content-mit-latex2edx-demo">https://github.com/mitocw/content-mit-latex2edx-demo</a></p>

<p>P.S. A handy way to automatically load your XML course content on github into
  Studio is
  via <a href="https://github.com/MITx/git2edx">git2edx</a>.
  Whenever changes are pushed to the repo, the course contents
  auto-import into Studio via a webhook.</p>
